		  one-sea winter adults at, or just before, freshwater
		  re-entry as the predicted weight at standard length. Two
		  independent 14-year time series for a single river stock
		  and for mixed, multiple stocks revealed almost identical
		  temporal patterns in growth condition variation, and an
		  overall trend decrease of 11?14% over the past decade.
		  Growth condition has fallen as SST anomaly has risen, and
