		  final condition on migratory return during the subsequent
		  summer months. Stored lipids are crucial for survival and
		  for the prespawning provisioning of eggs in freshwater, and
		  we show that under-weight individuals have
		  disproportionately low reserves. The poorest condition fish
		  (?30% under-weight) returned with lipid stores reduced by
		  ?80%. This study concurs with previous analyses of other
